since dander and many other allergens become trapped in hair , and shed hairs are light enough to spend considerable time airborne indoors before settling to the floor to be removed during housecleaning ( an activity which can , ironically , help them stay airborne ) , shedding of the coat is a typical way in which house - pets spread their allergens in a domestic environment .

